Executive Profile
Anthony F. Holler M.D.Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and President, Inviro MedicalAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 7 different industries.See Board Relationships65--
Background

		Dr. Anthony F. Holler, also known as Tony, M.D. serves as the Chief Executive Officer and President at Inviro Medical. Dr. Holler served as Treasurer at Response Biomedical Corp. until January 12, 2017 and served as its Interim Chief Executive Officer from September 16, 2014 until May 20, 2015. He previously served as the Chief Financial Officer at Response Biomedical Corp. Dr. Holler served as Chairman and Interim Chief Executive Officer of Inviro Medical Devices Limited. ... Dr. Holler served as Chief Executive Officer at ID Biomedical Corp. from March 27, 2001 to December 2005 and also served as its President. Dr. Holler has been the Independent Chairman of CRH Medical Corporation since December 21, 2005. He has been Chairman of Inviro Medical since August 2006 and Trevali Resources Corp. since October 2010. He serves as Non-Executive Chairman of Q2 Gold Resources Inc. and its Director since June 18, 2007. He served as the Chairman of Trevali Mining Corporation from October 2010 to February 14, 2014. Dr. Holler served as Non-Executive Chairman of Corriente Resources Inc. from 2003 to June 2010. He served as  Vice-Chairman of Response Biomedical Corp. since November 2015 until November 29, 2016. He serves as a Member of Advisory Board of Roadmap Capital Inc. Dr. Holler has been an Independent Director of CRH Medical Corporation since December 21, 2005 and Inviro Medical since April 27, 2006. He served as a Director of Response Biomedical Corp. since March 30, 2006  until November 29, 2016. He served as a Director of Neptune Technologies & Bioressources, Inc. since July 5, 2011. He served as a Director of Corriente Resources Inc. since September 10, 2003. Dr. Holler served as a Director of ID Biomedical Corporation since March 04, 1991. He served as an Emergency physician at University Hospital at University of British Columbia. Dr. Holler is a Member of the British Columbia College of Physicians and Surgeons. He holds a Bachelor of Science in 1975 and a Medical Degree in 1979 from the University of British Columbia.Read Full Background




